1
00:00:58,360 --> 00:00:59,160
All right.

2
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:01,780
Everyone can have some free time for now.

3
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,280
Don't go too far.

4
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:10,360
Thank you, sir.

5
00:01:16,039 --> 00:01:17,039
People always say

6
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:20,360
that human joys and sorrows are not connected.

7
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,160
But that's not true.

8
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,930
Our shared joys and sorrows

9
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,000
are all in poetry and literature.

10
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
From the most primitive epic poems

11
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,560
to Tang and Song poetry,

12
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,800
which of the stories they tell

13
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:37,560
are unfamiliar to us?

14
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,680
Dad Yin is right.

15
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,460
How could they be unfamiliar?

16
00:01:41,479 --> 00:01:43,160
Jiao Li can recite a few lines of

17
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:45,280
'The Return' anytime, anywhere.

18
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,960
Sir, why are you laughing at me too?

19
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,960
I even assisted you in class just now.

20
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:53,289
I'm not laughing at you.

21
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:55,759
I just think this language Naadam

22
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,400
was very effective

23
00:01:57,479 --> 00:01:58,880
and should be continued.

24
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,240
Stop laughing.

25
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,480
By the way,

26
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:06,920
did you distribute the money?

27
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:07,400
Yes.

28
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:09,639
I saw Aunt Guli and Uncle Tuoka

29
00:02:09,639 --> 00:02:11,300
being very active on Moments.

30
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,800
The profits from our live streams are out.

31
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,000
I thought everyone has been working hard lately,

32
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,640
so I wanted to make them happy.

33
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:18,440
You should.

34
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,079
The live streaming is on track now.

35
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,720
We want to change its format next.

36
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:25,320
Even in our daily videos,

37
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,040
we want to slowly de-brand.

38
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,640
Besides grassroots cadres,

39
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,680
I hope more Xia villagers

40
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,720
can participate in our

41
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:33,040
publicity matrix.

42
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,079
These words sound like

43
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,360
they are missing something.

44
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,079
Missing what?

45
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,320
Expressing emotions through scenery,

46
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,320
and embedding feelings in the scenery.

47
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:46,800
Whether you look up or down,

48
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,060
all you see are people.

49
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:52,180
You forgot to look at your surroundings.

50
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:03,640
How about

51
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,160
we look around?

52
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:07,120
Sure, I was thinking the same thing.

53
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:07,760
Let's go.

54
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:11,140
The pace of e-commerce

55
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,300
can be a bit faster.

56
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,720
Not only should we sell good products from Xinjiang,

57
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,160
but also let more people know

58
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:18,490
about the beautiful scenery of Xinjiang.

59
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:20,560
I know what to do.

60
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:23,280
Bortala.

61
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,800
The green grasslands

62
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,960
have wind and grass,

63
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:30,040
as well as lakes and snow mountains.

64
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:31,400
Perhaps all far-off places

65
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,560
can find here

66
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:34,410
the wilderness of their heart.

67
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,520
Xiaerxili,

68
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,040
the golden hillside.

69
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,720
Driving all the way here

70
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:44,360
feels like entering a computer wallpaper.

71
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,960
Grasslands, wild flowers,

72
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,120
and antelopes.

73
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:51,560
It is Xinjiang's last natural gallery.

74
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,130
Don't forget to take a break during your journey.

75
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:58,520
The bubbling springs in Wenquan County

76
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:00,480
always welcome you for a dip.

77
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,560
Under the blue sky,

78
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,480
and in front of the snowy mountains,

79
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:06,920
experience the leisurely comfort.

80
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:11,180
Come visit the bazaar.

81
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,680
Like a local,

82
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,720
sit down, eat a few baked buns,

83
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:16,779
and drink a bowl of salty milk tea.

84
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:24,520
There is always a queue for the tandoor.

85
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:26,360
Meatball soup paired with Youtazi

86
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:28,620
is the daily romance unique to Xinjiang.

87
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,000
Finally,

88
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,010
of course we must come to see it.

89
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:37,770
It is the last teardrop of the Atlantic Ocean.

90
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,640
A sapphire on sunny days,

91
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:43,280
it looks like jade when the sky is azure.

92
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:46,000
Every appearance makes you feel

93
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,880
that the world is worth it.

94
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:52,159
Vertical cover 3:4

95
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:54,200
All set.

96
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,659
How is it going?

97
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:00,480
I've uploaded all the places we've been to.

98
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:02,280
Let the netizens help us choose

99
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:04,000
the location for our outdoor live stream.

100
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,120
With interaction and participation,

101
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:08,040
I think our promotional goals beyond selling products

102
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:10,240
have already been achieved in advance.

103
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,640
When I was studying in Beijing,

104
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:20,010
I also liked to look up at the night sky.

105
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:23,200
But the city lights were too bright

106
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,380
to see the Milky Way and the stars.

107
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:27,800
But here,

108
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,730
you can see them just by looking up.

109
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,480
Do you like looking at the stars?

110
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,400
I do.

111
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:35,760
Look.

112
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:38,080
That's Lyra.

113
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,360
The bright stars around it

114
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,800
form a quadrilateral.

115
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,320
Do you see it?

116
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:46,640
Really.

117
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,240
At the zenith

118
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,400
is Perseus.

119
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:50,800
By the way,

120
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:52,360
the news said that at the end of this month,

121
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,490
there will be a Perseid meteor shower.

122
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,650
Have you ever seen a meteor shower?

123
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,840
I haven't.

124
00:05:58,920 --> 00:05:59,720
That's fine.

125
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,640
If the weather is good then,

126
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:03,120
we can pitch a tent here

127
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:03,980
and wait for it.

128
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:07,040
This is the biggest meteor shower in recent years.

129
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,600
The end of the month?

130
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,360
Yeah.

131
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:11,400
I... I think...

132
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,720
Is he pursuing you?

133
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:24,440
I noticed you haven't been answering calls lately.

134
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,560
I thought it was about a relationship.

135
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,840
Of course not.

136
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,720
He's the head of the e-commerce business at Shangle Group,

137
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,680
my former boss.

138
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:34,620
Is he asking you to go back to the company?

139
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:37,240
That's what he said at first.

140
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,600
But I refused.

141
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,280
I don't want to go back.

142
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,240
I never asked you

143
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,770
why you suddenly resigned and left the team to come here.

144
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,000
Actually,

145
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,800
I haven't contacted Father Yin for a long time.

146
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:57,050
Ever since my grandpa passed away,

147
00:06:57,159 --> 00:06:59,490
I've been working desperately every day.

148
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,410
Even if my boss uses me as a tool,

149
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,480
I wish I could spend all my time

150
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,960
on work.

151
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:08,500
I don't dare to stop for even a moment.

152
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,170
Because once I stop,

153
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,360
I'll feel very empty

154
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,930
and directionless.

155
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,360
Earlier,

156
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,440
I asked if you wanted to send goji berries

157
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,600
to your family and friends,

158
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,200
and your former colleagues.

159
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,200
I didn't know about all this.

160
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:27,280
I'm sorry.

161
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:32,170
My colleagues all think I'm too competitive.

162
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:33,840
They even

163
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:36,560
secretly created a group chat to vent their frustration.

164
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,880
I accidentally saw it.

165
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,080
That was when I realized

166
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,280
how much they

167
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,520
hated me.

168
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:45,000
Who exactly is Ren Zhen?

169
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,400
A useful tool for the boss.

170
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,960
A soulless working machine.

171
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:55,200
The day I got out of the car with my luggage

172
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,640
was the first time my colleagues offered to help me.

173
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:58,900
Ridiculous, isn't it?

174
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:04,960
I previously

175
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,880
interned out of town for half a year too.

176
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,560
I found that the people there

177
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:12,160
lived and worked with anxiety.

178
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:13,770
They didn't like

179
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,760
or want to understand others.

180
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,320
One day,

181
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:20,360
I felt I was going to become like that too.

182
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,560
I didn't like it,

183
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:23,040
so I came back.

184
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:25,960
That's great.

185
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:28,400
You found a place where you want to stay.

186
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,020
What about you?

187
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,120
I plan

188
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:38,770
to go back to Hangzhou after the outdoor livestream.

189
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,559
The leader of Shangle started his own company.

190
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:43,200
He invited me to be a partner.

191
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,370
You've decided?

192
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:51,490
That's good too.

193
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,540
Since you'll be a partner,

194
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,920
you can realize your value more.

195
00:08:57,200 --> 00:09:00,360
Once the livestream is developed, there won't be many variables.

196
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,200
With you here,

197
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:03,000
I believe whatever problems arise,

198
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,360
you can solve them.

199
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:11,370
The last crop of goji berries has been harvested.

200
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,540
It's getting cold.

201
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,440
It's time for me to go too.

202
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,930
Dad Yin, I've thought about it.

203
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,490
This is not the place for me to stay.

204
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,440
I want to wait

205
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:26,360
until the e-commerce business is stable,

206
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,490
and then I'll leave.

207
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:28,530
Are you sure?

208
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:37,120
I remember

209
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:39,680
when I was bullied by my classmates as a kid,

210
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,800
saying I had no parents,

211
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:44,440
you stood up to protect me.

212
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,640
Since then,

213
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:49,000
I called you

214
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,200
Dad Yin.

215
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:51,880
At that time,

216
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:53,840
you were so thin and small,

217
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,080
and so stubborn.

218
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,600
But you never cried.

219
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,880
Instead, calling me Dad Yin

220
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,800
made me cry.

221
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:07,960
Dad Yin,

222
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,240
do you know

223
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:11,120
what an empty urbanite is?

224
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,640
I am one.

225
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:15,960
I'm here,

226
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:18,240
really relaxed and happy.

227
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,440
But I know

228
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:22,200
this is just an escape.

229
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,000
If

230
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:26,280
I stay because I have no direction,

231
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:29,700
then one day when I meet a new problem,

232
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,600
I will escape

233
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,000
and leave again.

234
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:36,920
Who says escaping is wrong?

235
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:40,280
People can also find a new direction

236
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,000
while escaping.

237
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,880
Just follow your heart.

238
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:07,320
The Perseid meteor shower

239
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:09,160
is the most spectacular.

240
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:11,410
It's a pity you're leaving.

241
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,540
You won't be able to see it.

242
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:15,880
Shooting stars,

243
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,000
they flash by

244
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,580
and eventually fade away.

245
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:22,180
Just think of me as a meteor shower

246
00:11:22,680 --> 00:11:24,280
that fell over Xiacun.

247
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,970
The sky is clear now,

248
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,570
and I should disappear too.

249
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:30,650
Then what if this meteor shower

250
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:33,120
falls into my heart?
